definition.value: This is an AE which is one where the mother or the fetus has an increased risk of adverse outcomes compared to uncomplicated pregnancies.
This is an AE which is a health condition where the abdominal wall behind the navel is damaged and is also incarcerated.
This is an AE which is a rare genetic disorder of the small intestine that is inherited in an autosomal recessive pattern.
This is an AE which make it difficult to initiate breastfeeding for these high-risk infants.
This is an AE which is the ending of pregnancy where one or more babies leaves the uterus by passing through the vagina or by Caesarean section and is traumatic .
This is an AE which is designed to allow the remaining fetus(es) to develop after premature expulsion of the first twin in the second trimester of pregnancy.
This is an AE which is a common complication of pregnancy that has been associated with a variety of adverse perinatal outcomes.

This is an AE which refer to a disability classification used in educational settings that allows educational institutions to provide special education and related services to students who have displayed poor social and/or academic progress.
This is an AE which is an effect of kernicterus.
This is an AE which corresponds to an impairment of urinary transport that can lead to renal dysfunction if not treated.
This is an AE which is a potential emergency.
This is an AE which is any part of an animal or plant that is involved in sexual reproduction and is  enlarged.
This is an AE which is cancer that develops from breast tissue and occurs invasive ductal.
This is an AE which is cancer that develops from breast tissuec and is hormone refractory .
This is an AE which is defined as an endometrium of > 5 mm discovered on ultrasound in a postmenopausal woman who is not bleeding.
This is an AE which is the medical use of probes called sounds to increase the inner diameter of the urethra and to locate obstructions in it.
This is an AE which is the partial or total loss of reproductive and hormonal function of the ovaries before age 40 because of folliclular (egg producing area) dysfunction or early loss of eggs.

This is an AE which refers a band of coagulative necrosis at the choriodecidual interphase, is a histologic lesion of unclear pathogenesis that has been reported in placentas from preeclampsia, preterm premature rupture of membranes, and preterm abruption.
This is an AE which is a collection of pus that has built up within the tissue of the vaginal.
This is an AE which might accurately reflect an acidotic state in the vaginal synapses and perineural space.
This is an AE which is an extraordinarily rare form of cancer that develops in the tissue of the vagina.
This is an AE which is excessive growth of yeast in the vagina that results in irritation.
This is an AE which is a pathological condition that affects part or all of the vagina.

This is an AE which is any of various types of abnormal growth or development of cells (microscopic scale) and/or organs (macroscopic scale), and/or the abnormal histology or anatomical structure presumably resulting from such growth such as vaginal dysplasia.
This is an AE which is an emission or expulsion of air from the vagina.
This is an AE which refers irregular tear-like wounds caused by some blunt trauma on the vaginal .
This is an AE which is any damage or abnormal change in the tissue of vaginal , usually caused by disease or trauma.
This is an AE which is a cancer of the vulva, the outer portion of the female genitals.
This is an AE which is caused by one or more volatilized chemical compounds on the vaginal  that are generally found in low concentrations .
This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in the vaginal  tissue.
This is an AE which refers a transient abnormal enlargement of a vaginal  part or area not caused by a tumor.
This is an AE which occurs when the normal lactobacilli of the vagina are replaced by mostly anaerobic bacteria.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the vagina and vulva caused by bacterial.

This is an AE which is a facultatively anaerobic Gram-variable rod that is involved, together with many other bacteria, mostly anaerobic, in bacterial vaginosis in some women as a result of a disruption in the normal vaginal microflora.
This is an AE which is a closed sac on the vulva, having a distinct envelope and division compared with the nearby tissue.
This is an AE which is a cancer of the vulva, the outer portion of the female genitals.
This is an AE which is a closed sac on the vulva, having a distinct envelope and division compared with the nearby tissue and it become disorder.
This is an AE which is blood escaping from the circulatory system from damaged vulval blood vessels.
This is an AE which refers irregular tear-like wounds caused by some blunt trauma. Lacerations and incisions may appear linear (regular) or stellate (irregular) such as vulval  lacerations.
This is an AE which is an open sore located on the genital area, which includes the vulva, penis, perianal region, or anus.

This is an AE which is any of various types of abnormal growth or development of cells (microscopic scale) and/or organs (macroscopic scale), and/or the abnormal histology or anatomical structure presumably resulting from such growth such as vulvar dysplasia.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the vulva, the external female mammalian genitalia that include the labia majora, labia minora, clitoris, and introitus (the entrance to the vagina).

This is an AE which is  related to neuropathic pain and associated to various degrees of vulvar mucosal hypersensitivity (mostly in the vestibular area), pelvic floor muscles dysfunction, a disorder of general perception of pain and/or various complex regional pain syndromes.
